Project:Covid Data Analysis

The source of the data is from JohnsHopkins University. There are three datasets first is for the confirmed covid cases which consists of 266 rows and 248 columns, second data is recovered covid cases which consist of 253 rows and 248 columns, and last dataset is death covid cases consist of 266 rows and 248 columns

The columns are

Province/State,Country/Region,Lat,Long,and the rest of the columns containing the dates.

Renaming the columns Province/Country into Province and Country/Region into Country

In [6]:
def Import_Covid19data(filepath):
    data = filepath
    data = pd.read_csv(data)
    data.rename(columns={'Province/State':'Province','Country/Region':'Country'},inplace = True)
    return data

Transforming given data by adding a column for dates

In [7]:
def transform_Covid19data(data):
    data = pd.melt(
    frame = data,
    id_vars = ['Province','Country','Lat','Long','Status'],
    var_name = 'Date',
    value_name = 'Count'
    )
    return data

selecting top 15 countries that has highest number of confirmed,recovered,and death covid cases

In [29]:
def Top15CountriesCases(Status):
    Top15Countries = data[(data['Status']==Status) & (data.index==max(data[data['Status']==Status].index))].sort_values(by='Count',ascending = False).head(15)[['Country','Count']]
    return Top15Countries
In [30]:
Top15CountriesRecovered = Top15CountriesCases('Recovered')
Top15CountriesConfirmed = Top15CountriesCases('Confirmed')
Top15CountriesDeaths = Top15CountriesCases('Death')
In [31]:
def Display_Top15Country(Top15Countries,Status):
    Top15Countries = Top15Countries.reset_index()
    Top15Countries = Top15Countries[['Country','Count']]
    date = max(data[data['Status']==Status].index)
    date = date.date()
    print(Status +' cases till:',date)
    return Top15Countries

def horizontal_bar_chart(Top15CountriesDeaths, x, y, title, x_label, y_label, color):
    fig = px.bar(Top15CountriesDeaths, x=x, y=y, orientation='h', title=title, 
                 labels={x.name: x_label,
                         y.name: y_label}, color_discrete_sequence=[color])
    fig.update_layout(yaxis={'categoryorder': 'total ascending'})
    fig.show()

In [45]:
import numpy as np
tranformeddata = pd.pivot_table(
            data,
            index = [data.index,'Province','Country','Lat','Long'],
            columns = 'Status',

Time Series Forecasting using FB Prophet:

It is a procedure for forecasting time series data based on an additive model where non-linear trends are fit with yearly, weekly, and daily seasonality. It works with time series data that have strong seasonal effects and several seasons of historical data

Conclusion

In this project, we are going to work with the COVID19 dataset, published by John Hopkins University, which consists of the data related to the cumulative number of confirmed cases, recovered cases, death cases per day, in each country around the world. We merge these three datasets to see the relationship between the spread of the virus in various countries. Then we select a particular country and finding the covid confirmed, recovered and death cases in that country. The results give the scenario of pandemic and may vary with time depending upon the actions taken by the government. Here FB prophet is used for predicting the future trends
